00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,634
Hi.Just hang on.

250
00:13:53,919 --> 00:13:54,908
[CHUCKLES]

251
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,832
-Small world.
-You did talk to her, didn't you?

252
00:13:56,999 --> 00:13:59,911
Of course, I did.
I talked and talked and talked.

253
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:04,033
Hey. Look at Leonard
in his fancy-ass grown-up clothes.

254
00:14:05,799 --> 00:14:06,834
Way to go, Priya.

255
00:14:06,999 --> 00:14:10,389
For once, he doesn't look like
a mannequin in the boys department.

256
00:14:10,959 --> 00:14:11,948
[PENNY AND PRIYA CHUCKLE]

257
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:14,315
Hey, did he tell you
I saved the silk shirt?

258
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:15,713
No, he did not.

259
00:14:15,879 --> 00:14:19,554
He was gonna throw it in the washing
machine with his Spiderman underwear.

260
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:22,430
That's our Lenny, huh? Ha, ha.

261
00:14:22,599 --> 00:14:24,829
Yes, that's our Lenny.

262
00:14:24,999 --> 00:14:26,796
So how's the food here?

263
00:14:27,159 --> 00:14:29,992
Oh, wow, that is really, really good.

264
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,754
Okay. You guys are on a date.
We can hang out anytime.

265
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:33,909
Have fun.

266
00:14:34,079 --> 00:14:35,194
-Bye.
PRIYA: Good night.

267
00:14:35,359 --> 00:14:38,271
Oh, that's hot, hot, hot.

268
00:14:41,079 --> 00:14:45,118
Whew. It really sneaks up on you, huh?
All right, I gotta go.

269
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:51,152
It is pretty spicy.

270
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,998
Oh, I've been meaning to tell you...

271
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,832
...I figured out your magic trick.

272
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,597
-Really?
-Oh, yes.

273
00:15:00,759 --> 00:15:02,989
In fact, I improved upon it.

274
00:15:03,879 --> 00:15:06,313
I'd love to see that.
How about you, Raj?

275
00:15:06,479 --> 00:15:08,754
Beefaroni and a show?
How do you turn that down?

276
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,194
[HOWARD CHUCKLES]

277
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,069
All right.

278
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,559
[CLEARS TH ROAT]

279
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:18,395
-Pick a card.
-Okay, hmm....

280
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,832
Bippity-boppity-boo.

281
00:15:20,999 --> 00:15:22,273
[BEEPS]

282
00:15:30,599 --> 00:15:32,715
What's with the wand and the beep?

283
00:15:32,879 --> 00:15:36,508
The wand is called showmanship,
and the beep is none of your business.

284
00:15:38,199 --> 00:15:39,188
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

285
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,112
Oh, excuse me.
I'm getting a text message...

286
00:15:41,279 --> 00:15:43,793
...completely unrelated
to this magic trick.

287
00:15:44,759 --> 00:15:47,148
Oh, look, my dry cleaning's ready.

288
00:15:47,319 --> 00:15:50,834
And your card
was the five of spades. Ta-da!

289
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,555
These cards have barcodes on them.

290
00:15:54,719 --> 00:15:57,313
The wand is a reader.
It's transmitting to your phone.

291
00:16:02,199 --> 00:16:03,996
I said, "ta-da." Show's over.

292
00:16:05,399 --> 00:16:08,789
That's pathetic. Let me show you
how a real magician does it.

293
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:11,918
Raj, take a card.
Don't let me see it.

294
00:16:12,079 --> 00:16:14,070
Okay.

295
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,753
Three of clubs.

296
00:16:15,919 --> 00:16:18,194
Son of a gun,
you're blowing my mind.

297
00:16:22,039 --> 00:16:23,711
Bippity-Boppity-Booya

298
00:16:23,879 --> 00:16:25,551
[HOWARD AND RAJESH CHUCKLE]

299
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:29,711
That does it. I'm getting uranium.

300
00:16:33,439 --> 00:16:37,591
-You ever gonna tell him?
-Maybe. When it stops being fun.

301
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,839
So never.

302
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,993


303
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:51,117
-Hey, I was just on my way to work.
-lt's not important. It can wait.

304
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:53,157
No, it's all right. Walk me down.

305
00:16:53,319 --> 00:16:54,388
So, what's up?

306
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:57,393
Uh, I kind of have a problem
I was hoping you could help me with.

307
00:16:57,560 --> 00:17:00,313
PENNY: Sure, anything.
-Move out.

308
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,396
PENNY: What?
-Not far.

309
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:07,792
Hey, if you ever wanna start a family,
La Canada has some great schools.

310
00:17:07,959 --> 00:17:10,837
Okay, I'm not moving anywhere.
What the hell is this all about?

311
00:17:10,999 --> 00:17:12,876
Why does it have to be
about anything?

312
00:17:13,080 --> 00:17:17,358
Can't a fellow ask his buddy to relocate,
no questions asked?

313
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,318
Oh, for God's sake, Leonard,
this is about Priya, isn't it?

314
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,357
She doesn't want me
hanging out with you.

315
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,988
Yes. There, I said it.

316
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:27,709
Okay, look.

317
00:17:27,879 --> 00:17:30,473
-I happen to like your girlfriend.
-And she likes you.

318
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,790
-No, she doesn't.
-Not really, no.

319
00:17:32,959 --> 00:17:36,110
It doesn't matter. From now on,
I will keep my distance from you.

320
00:17:36,279 --> 00:17:38,839
Hold on. What kind of
distance are we talking about?

321
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,149
Because we are neighbors.

322
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:43,312
I mean, I can hear the toilet flush
in your apartment.

323
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:46,074
-You can hear my toilet flush?
-I don't listen for it...

324
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:49,835
...but it's nice to know
everything's okay with your plumbing.

325
00:17:50,679 --> 00:17:52,590
The building's plumbing.

326
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,354
Leonard, I get it.
You're in a new relationship.

327
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:58,353
I'm happy for you. Why don't we
shake hands and part friends?

328
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,839
Well, now hold on.

329
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,069
How about this?

330
00:18:01,239 --> 00:18:04,117
How about we still hang out,
but on the down low?

331
00:18:06,159 --> 00:18:09,549
-Are you really that kind of guy?
-No.

332
00:18:09,719 --> 00:18:12,995
I actually felt kind of silly
just saying "on the down low."

333
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,433
Goodbye, Leonard.

334
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:21,872
Penny, wait.

335
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,991
Damn contacts.

336
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,711
Incoming.

337
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,596
-Hi.
-Hey.

338
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,512
Hello.

339
00:18:41,959 --> 00:18:44,075
Why so glum, chum?

340
00:18:44,719 --> 00:18:47,916
Apparently, you can't hack
into a government supercomputer...

341
00:18:48,079 --> 00:18:49,671
...and then try to buy uranium...

342
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:54,197
...without the Department of Homeland
Security tattling to your mother.

343
00:18:58,559 --> 00:19:00,914
Oh, that's too bad.
Figure out the magic trick yet?

344
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,116
[MOCKINGLY]
"Figure out the magic trick yet?"

345
00:19:04,079 --> 00:19:06,035
-Want me to tell you how to do it?
-No.

346
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,679
I'll show you one more time.

347
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:10,798
-Raj?
-Hang on.

348
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:15,598
This time do it with me, so I can
make sure there's no monkey business.

349
00:19:17,799 --> 00:19:18,788
All right.

350
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,998
-Two of hearts.
-I hate you.

351
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,555
[RAJESH AND HOWARD LAUGHING]

352
00:19:41,199 --> 00:19:43,918
Yeah, he's gonna win the Nobel Prize.

